        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 12:03PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 1203 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dillen, or 20 miles northeast of Clarksville, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ben Hur...                        Fort Douglas...
Haw Creek Falls Campground...     Nogo...
Dillen...                         Treat...
Moore...                          Solo...
Sand Gap...                       Bertha...
Lurton...                         Smyrna...
Rosetta...                        Mineral Springs Recreation Area...
Simpson...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
